<lb corresp="#b4"/><gap reason="lost"/><foreign xml:lang="san"><w><supplied>pūti</supplied></w><w><supplied>kar</supplied>o<supplied>t</supplied>i</w><w>ba<supplied>ndhanam</supplied></w></foreign><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] [and in] always [being] a disciple (of the Buddhas). [TB] ([and in] always [being] a disciple) of the Buddhas.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] [would] (not) [be] (sufficient wealth) for a single man [SKT] (having recognised) this, (one should act right)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] (for him who has fierce desire, and) contemplates (pleasant things)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] but he who is pleased with the quiescence (of doubts)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (he) makes [his] fetter (rotten)</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>117-119</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:chakravarti1930"/><citedRange>29-34</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>19-20</citedRange></bibl></note><note type="remarks">On <ref target="http://idp.bl.uk/database/oo_loader.a4d?pm=IOL%20Toch%20715" type="external">IDP</ref>, recto and verso are reversed.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">Uv.2.18d <hi>buddhānāṃ śrāvakaḥ sadā</hi></note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">Uv.2.19c-d <hi>vittaṃ taṃ nālam ekasya etaj jñātvā samaṃ caret</hi></note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">Uv.3.1b <hi>tīvrarāgasya śubhānudarśinaḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">Uv.3.2a <hi>vitarkavyupaśame tu yo rato</hi></note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">Uv.3.2d <hi>sa tu khalu pūti karoti bandhanam</hi> (see <bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1968"/></bibl>: Corrigenda zu Band I).</note></p>
         </div>
